3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The study of reversible computation is closely related to the study of logic gates and circuits, which is a topic in logic in computer science. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The study of reversible computation is also related to the study of computational complexity, as it has implications for the efficiency of algorithms. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The study of cellular automata is a topic in data structures and algorithms, as it involves the manipulation of arrays of cells.
